title: For Sale:  Ammo/reloading prices
postcontent:
Here's the deal people....I'm all for the free market, capitalism, supply and demand, etc. I'm not here to hate on the people who sell ammo and reloading supplies at jacked up prices. If I had the time or the desire to get up early and stand in line for ammo at Cabelas or Gander Mountain, just so I can turn around and sell it for 100-200% profit, I probably would. That's not robbery, it's just business. It's not these people's fault that ammo prices are so high. It's our fault, the consumers. 

Do yourselves a favor, STOP BUYING FROM THESE PEOPLE. Go without shooting for a couple weeks if you have to. If there's no demand, the prices WILL go down. The only reason these people go to such lengths to purchase ammo and supplies is because they know people will pay. If we stop paying, they'll stop clearing off the shelves before the delivery truck leaves, and there will be some normally priced ammo left for the rest of us. The supply is there, it's just being bought up by all these price-gougers (Many of whom don't even buy the ammo to shoot it, some of whom may not even own guns) and sold at ridiculous prices to suckers like us. Don't encourage them, DON'T BUY! I guarantee you they'll get tired of buying up ammo that is useless and worthless to them. Get yourself enough to last through a SHTF situation, then stop buying. See what happens.

To all the price-gougers....like I said, I'm not here to bash you all, if people are willing to pay double the retail price, why wouldn't you buy up as much as you can and then sell it for a profit? But seriously, don't get up at 4:00am, be the first one at the door when the local Gander Mountain opens, buy all the ammo before anyone else gets a chance, and then act like you're doing us a favor when you sell it for double and triple what you paid. You'll be doing us a real favor by only buying what you can shoot, and leaving the rest for someone else. 

Let's get our act together here people.
